dct_description_sm: Alternate title: Kato. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. Compiled in 1944 from aerial photography dated November 1943 and March 1944 by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2214 III, 1944. Additional information from intelligence data. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to Lai-chia. Relief shown by 10 meter contours. Three classes of roads or trails, two classes of railroads, and areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. Military grid. Includes index to boundaries, coverage diagram, and glossary. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. AMS 1. South Decimal Degree 22.400000. North Decimal Degree 22.450000. West Decimal Degree 120.533333. East Decimal Degree 120.583333.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1944.
